parameters:
"Welcome back, Rise. Were you able to report to Gugukas, the
Minister of Justice?"

"That was the plan, but it seems he had to rush off to an
urgent case in another town. He's not here right now."

Suelle returned to town and headed to Selphie's room to
research hypnotic spells.

Rise went to report about the brainwashing to Gugukas, the
Minister of Justice, but it seems Gugukas was not there.

"So I tried to have the staff contact him through the
communication device, but it seems they couldn't get
through. He's probably in a facility where communication is
impossible."

"A facility where communication is impossible... Maybe a
prison or a confidential facility?"

"Could it be that there's been some progress with Tina Onee-
san?"

"I thought so too and asked, but it seems he left without
telling his subordinates the details."

"He seemed to be in a hurry because of some unavoidable
business, so it's quite possible it has something to do with
Tina."

"I see. Then we'll ask Gugukas, the Minister of Justice,
when he gets back."

"Right. If it's related to Tina, he'll surely contact us
too."

"For now, let's put Gugukas aside and contact Selphie. I'd
like to report about Tina's situation as soon as
possible..."

"Selphie-san is undercover, so we can't just contact her
from our end."

"But she said she would contact us within the day, so maybe
she'll get in touch by tonight?"

"Then we should tell her about the brainwashing when she
does."

"Yeah, for now we'll do what we can to research the spell
used on Tina while waiting for Selphie-san's contact."

And so Suelle and Rise began their respective research while
waiting for Selphie's contact.

"Hmm, it's already this late? It's difficult to investigate
without any clues."
Stretching, Suelle loosens his stiff body.

"It's about to be a new day. Has Selphie not contacted us
yet?"

"She left in the morning, so we should be getting a contact
from her soon..."
Beep beep beep!! Beep beep beep!!
"Ah, right on time, there's a message from Selphie!!"
"As expected of Selphie, her timing is impeccable."

"Let's see... She's using video communication, so I'll
project it onto the wall."

With that said, Suelle skillfully sets up the communication
device and starts the transmission.

The screen switches and a woman appears, speaking in a
cheerful voice.

She is beautiful, but Suelle senses something dangerous
about her.

"What happened next? Oh, Selphie-chan was writhing in
ecstasy, climaxing hundreds of times already."

"Boys like that sort of thing, don't they? You want to see
it, right?"
"But too bad, if you want to see more, you'll have to pay."

Staring at the giggling woman, Suelle is simply dumbfounded
and speechless.

"Hehe, but this time, since Suelle-kun was so helpful when
Selphie-chan and I made our slave contract, I decided to
show you as a special treat."
The woman pouts as if she wanted more of a reaction.

Catching on the woman's words in the video, Suelle asks back
with a sense of unease.

"Well, you'll notice what's going on around you
eventually... Let's just call it a future pleasure, shall
we?"

"What are you talking about, what does this mean?!! Who are
you?!!"
"Oh my, men who are too eager can be such a turn-off."

"Well, I suppose I can at least tell you my name. I'm
Bellra. Nice to meet you?"

"Ah, perhaps you've become interested in me? Well, after
seeing such a lewd pig, it's not surprising you'd switch
your attention to me."

She continues to speak provocatively with a laugh, as if to
taunt without getting discouraged.
She ponders the question with a thoughtful 'hmm'.

"Why, you ask? There's no particular reason... If I had to
say, maybe it's just for fun?"
"I was also curious about what a hero party would be like."

Suelle couldn't comprehend what the woman who called herself
Bellra was saying.

He understood the words, but not their meaning. Suelle felt
a chill at the madness of her thoughts, which were beyond
any normal reasoning.

"A game... To do such terrible things to everyone for that,
I'll never forgive you!!"

"Is that so? Well, I wasn't exactly looking for your
forgiveness anyway."

"But if you insist so much, perhaps we should play a game
together."
She raises a finger as if to indicate a simple rule.

"If you can save all the members of the hero party... Hmm,
then I'll quietly let myself be captured. How about that?"

Suelle didn't want to agree to Bellra's terms. Especially
not to such a distasteful game.

However, if it meant saving Tina and Selphie, then he felt a
rising desire to do just that.

"I will definitely save my companions!! I won't let you do
as you please anymore!!"

Does she think it's impossible to save them? Or is she just
watching with a sense of amusement to see how things will
turn out?

As always, Bellra on the other side of the screen just keeps
a composed smile on her face.

"Then go ahead and find Tina-chan and Selphie-chan and
rescue them, okay?"

"Ufufu, you better hurry or it might become something
irreversible, you know?"

Leaving behind words of anticipation, the communication was
unilaterally cut off.

Suelle slumped down towards the wall that no longer showed
anything.

What awaited the slumped Suelle was the reality that his
companions had been captured.

No words of encouragement came to mind. No words of comfort
either.

Yet Rise knew what words should be spoken. She took a deep
breath in.

Rise shouted at Suelle with a loud voice that echoed
throughout the room.

"You just said you'd save them!! Everyone is relying on
you!!"
Rise must have been pained by the horrific scene as well.

Nevertheless, she raised her voice and scolded him to get
Suelle back on his feet.

Turning towards Rise, Suelle was glaring at her with tears
faintly showing in his eyes.

"(That's right, I need to pull myself together now. There's
not a second to spare feeling down at a time like this!!)"

Knowing Rise's feelings, Suelle realized that now was the
time he had to stand firm.
"Thank you, Rise. I'll definitely rescue them."

"Alright, first we need to organize the information we
have."

Now they needed to find a breakthrough with the limited
information available.

The two of them tried to remember everything that happened,
not letting any piece of information slip by.

"Come to think of it, those guys mentioned something about
brainwashing with ancient magic formulas."

"Yeah, ancient magic formulas. They're supposed to be a
completely different kind of power from modern magic, both
in essence and structure."

"So, maybe Tina was brainwashed because Fullbody couldn't
recognize the ancient magic formula as a skill."

"But even if it didn't recognize it as a skill, if it was an
attack, Fullbody should have automatically repelled it
randomly, right?"

Rise thought that even if Fullbody couldn't decipher the
skill, if it was an attack, it should automatically react.

"In that video Selphie showed earlier, there was someone
talking about a 'contract of servitude'."

"He didn't say slave brainwashing or servitude
brainwashing... he said 'contract of servitude'."

"I've read about it in documents before. There are ancient
magic formulas that use contracts,"

"And it seems there are some that maintain a brainwashed
state indefinitely once the brainwashing is completed during
the contract period."

Suelle added that it was mostly uncertain information
shrouded in mystery.

"I think they probably avoided Fullbody's reactive attack by
using a contract."

"I see, if that's the case, it seems like our opponent did
quite a bit of research."

If such a technique can be used, then it's entirely possible
for even Tina to be caught off guard.

Especially since Tina's Fullbody is prone to showing
openings due to its nature when dealing with such tricky
tactics.

Rise also finds herself troubled by how critical the
situation has become.

"Sorry, Rise. Do you mind if I hole up in my room for a
little while?"
After pondering for a while, Suelle opens up to Rise.

However, it wasn't just about shutting himself away; Rise
could feel his determination to find a solution in his eyes.

"Yeah, there's something I want to try by applying the
device I was working on after watching the videos of Tina
and Selphie."

"Though, it's not something that can pinpoint their location
or anything."

"Okay, understood. Then I'll look into Tina and Selphie's
whereabouts."

"But I can't just leave you and expand my search area... I'm
not sure how much I can do."

"Anyway, leave the search for them to me and you focus on
whatever this application for the device is."
(It's frustrating, but there's only so much I can do...)

(Suelle always lacks confidence in himself. He's convinced
that everyone around him is amazing...)

(But you know? In times like this, the most reliable person
is Suelle... Everyone thinks so.)

"Now that the two of them are gone, let's not rush and make
sure we come up with a solid plan."

There's no time to be downhearted. Both of them resolve to
do what they can and move forward.

"Then, I'll start with the redesign first. Probably in about
5 days, I'll know what materials we need, so I'd like you to
come with me to get them then."
"Understood, call me when the time comes."

And so, Suelle and the others began to move to save their
comrades.

A few hours before Suelle and the others made their resolve
and stood up.
This is the whole story of Selphie a few hours earlier.
